  test: /\.(png|svg|jpg|jpeg|gif)/i,
  type: "asset/resource",
  generator: {
    filename: ({ filename }) => {
      const srcPath = 'src/assets/images'; // path to source images
      const regExp = new RegExp(`[\\\\/]?(?:${path.normalize(srcPath)}|node_modules)[\\\\/](.+?)$`);
      const assetPath = path.dirname(regExp.exec(filename)[1].replace('@', '').replace(/\\/g, '/'));

      return `images/${assetPath}/[name][ext]`;
    },
  }
},
```

The destructed `filename` argument is the source file. It can be an absolute or a relative.

